text: Creatonotos gangis, also known as the Baphomet moth, is a species of moth that is usually seen in Western Australia and South East Asia. == Description == The moth has two light brown wings, and a red abdomen with black spots. Males can have four long black coremata at the end of the abdomen, when inflated. The male moths have the coremata so they can attract female moths. == References == Category:Moths
title: Creatonotos gangis
